// Link

// Basic way to move between pages in React Router.

// It changes the URL without reloading the page.

// Use when you just want navigation, no styling for active links.

// <Link to="/about">About</Link>

// ðŸ”¹ NavLink

// Works like Link, but adds an active class (or lets you style differently) when the route is active.

// Perfect for menus or navigation bars.

// <NavLink to="/about" className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? "active-link" : ""}>
//   About
// </NavLink>


// If you have a navbar â†’ use NavLink.

// ðŸ”¹ navigate (from useNavigate)

// A hook, not a component.

// Use it when you want to redirect programmatically (e.g., after login, logout, or a button click).

